jobs_results.title: Salesforce Developer
jobs_results.description:
1. RESPONSIBILITIES

· Determine business, functional and technical requirements; and participate in application design, configuration, testing and deployment.

· Perform configuration and customization of the Salesforce.com platform.

· Participate in efforts to develop and execute testing, training and documentation.

· Produce tangible deliverables such as requirement specifications, design deliverables, status reports, project plans for project and change initiatives.

· Utilize best practices to perform operational support, enhancements, and bug fixes as needed to the Salesforce.com platform.

· Follow all standard operating procedures and maintain updated ticketing for events, incidents, requests, changes, problem, etc.

· Proactively engage on continuous improvement efforts for application design, support and practice development efforts.

· Provide technical assistance and end-user troubleshooting for bug fixes, enhancements, and how-to assistance.

· Act as a point of... escalation for Service Desk and NOC ticketing for advanced issue resolution.

JOB REQUIREMENTS

Academic Education & Experience

· Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering or equivalent.

· At least 3 years of working experience as a Salesforce Developer.

· Experience in vendor, service, stakeholders and people management.

· Experience in agile software development and support mid to large scale Salesforce projects.

· Direct working experience on Salesforce platforms on CRM and Digital Marketing projects.

· Knowledge and experience with complex business systems integration as well as object-oriented design patterns and development.

· Experience with Agile development methodologies such as XP/SCRUM.

Skills and knowledge

· Expertise in core web technolocies including HTML5, Javascript and jQuery.

· Software engineering skills with Force.com platform (Apex, VisualForce, SOQL, Unit Testing)

· Software engineering skills with Java SE & EE (Java, JSF, SQL) preferred.

· Knowledge of relational databases, data modelling, and ETL tools.

· Have a good problem-solving skill that is able analyze issues from multiple perspectives and derive pragmatic and comprehensive solutions to problems in sometimes an ambiguous environment.

· Team player who can communicate effectively, to bring forth the ideas, plans and strategies to other stakeholders in order forge common goals and concretize deliverables.

· Able to work highly independently and good project management skills.

· Desire to work within a fast-paced, collaborative, and team-based support environment.

​

jobs_results.title: Intermediate Software Engineer
jobs_results.description:
Position

Risks and Finance department is responsible for development and maintenance of Compliance, Referentials, Counterparty/Credit Risks and Finance applications used by worldwide users, composed of the following divisions :
• Compliance IT handles Business Compliance & Financial Security application portfolio, based on internal and regulatory models
• Referentials IT covers Know Your Customer processes & Counterparty referential management
• Credit Risk IT covers Front office Applications, Credit Decision Processing tool, Global Authorization Repository system and Default History Data Base
• Counterparty Risk IT handles applications responsible for risk data collection, risk calculation and monitoring for CACIB worldwide
• Finance IT is responsible for applications handling financial accounting and liqauidity and yied financial risks for CACIB worldwide.

Risks and Finance applications are all in-house developments.

Main Pre-requisites
Core programming langages: .Net, Java... SQL
Methodologies
Agile and/or Iterative development lifecycles
Continuous Integration / Continuous Delivery
Latest technology stacks
Data Science : Machine Learning, Business Intelligence
Batch processing : Big Data, Fast Data, ElasticSearch, Kafka
Web : Angular, ReactJS, JQuery, Node.Js

Main responsibilities
• Study, evaluate, analyze business requirements and functional specifications.
• Provide detailed estimation for Software Engineering solutions
• Implement and Test Software Engineering solutions
• Enable and support functional and user acceptance testing
• Support applications in production - analyze and resolve issues as they arise

The activity provided will have to comply with the CA-CIB Policy

Our service spectrum includes enterprise solution consulting, business intelligence, business process automation and managed services. Given our decade of success we have evolved to become one of the top trusted providers in Singapore and service a client base across banking and financial services, insurance, information technology, healthcare, retail and supply chain. We are currently looking to hire a Pega Developer. This is an exciting opportunity to expand your skill set, achieve job satisfaction and work-life balance. More details as below.
JOB TYPE:
1-year renewable contract.

Roles and Responsibilities
Work along with Snr/Lead in developing/maintaining Pega based applications.
Implementation and development of Pega content type models, workflows, templates, and components, and use permissions.
creating process flows using various shapes/smart shapes
Development Using Pega... Rules -UI, Activities and Flows, Declaratives, Decision, Validation, Reports
Defining application cases and processes that defines the case life cycle
Creating integration rules to interact with external systems

Assist in deploying applications to Dev, UAT, Production environments and migrations.

Strong team player to project and application team to ensure key deliverables meet customer expectation
Demonstrate team synergy and harmonize team integration
A pro-active approach to work, with a positive can-do attitude

Minimum 2 years of relevant development experience in developing web-based applications using Java
Development experience in technologies such as HTML5, XML, JavaScript, jQuery, CSS3, web services
Pega Certified System Architect / Pega Certified Senior System Architect would be an advantage.

Strong hands-on experience in troubleshootinging skills.
Strong analytical and problem solving skills.

Detail-oriented, strong work ethic and high standard of excellence.

You will be remunerated with an excellent base salary and entitled to attractive company benefits. Additionally, you will get the opportunity to enjoy a fun and collaborative work environment, alongside a strong career progression.

jobs_results.title: Staff Software Engineer ( L3 - Etl & Reporting)
jobs_results.description:
About Job

CTC Undisclosed Job Location Singapore Experience 7 - 10 yrs

Description

Job Description and Responsibilities

Visa Resolve Online (VROL) is a web-based and System Interface application that enforces the rules and workflow of disputes for Visa Clients. VROL is a mandated service that is crucial to the Visa brand promise of providing secure and reliable payment services. The system ensures that cardholders, merchants, and financial institutions have a clear dispute process, and makes resolution of disputed transactions fast and easy. As a member of the VROL Level 3 development team you will:

Develop ETL solutions for Visa Resolve Online including ETL processing, billing, reports, analytics, financial processing, merchant data processing
Develop complex SQL routines and Jaspersoft reports and fine tune existing graphs and reports
Provide third and fourth level support for incident management activities in both production and client certification environment with root cause... analysis, identifying the solution and propose changes to prevent similar issues in the future
Design, Develop, Document and maintain tools and utilities for automation and enhanced monitoring
Support, maintain, and enhance the production and Member testing systems presentment to ensure services are provided as per SLA
Perform technical analysis, review technical design, coding, unit testing, and support activities
Participate in production implementations, providing all necessary support to ensure successful resolution of issues
Collaborate closely and foster partnerships with second level support, development, and Test Engineering teams to fast track issue resolutions, and ensure efficient use of resources
Collaborate with upstream/downstream systems and technology leads to design and implement solutions that meet business needs
Translate business requirements and conceptual approach into technical design;
create technical specifications, and implementation plans;
Foster partnerships with second level support, Development, and Test Engineering teams to fast track issue resolutions, and ensure efficient use of resources
Contribute to the development of requirements, specifications, and use cases for assigned projects
Work with QA teams to ensure quality of code in test cycles, and provide support in resolving defects in a timely manner
Support business partners for user acceptance testing, present solutions to key stakeholders and demonstrate working software to leads and management
Follow existing application standards, conventions, and best practices as part of the existing SDLC
Develop Job Schedule and create runbook for operations to handle the issues/failure for the features and jobs developed
Ensure that applications and code are compliant with Visa security requirements and code is developed as per the development methodology
Collaborate and work with resources deployed globally, including staff, vendors, and offshore partners; and work with limited direction
Help drive continuous improvement around processes and technical capabilities using various tools and leverage production statistics by working with Architecture, QA, Operations and external groups to the program

Qualifications

Basic Qualifications

4 years of work experience with a Bachelors Degree or at least 2 years of work experience with an Advanced degree (e.g. Masters, MBA, JD, MD) or 0 years of work experience with a PhD degree in Computer Science or similar field in the financial services industry.

Preferred Qualifications

7-10 years of work experience and a Bachelors Degree or 6 years of work experience with an Advanced Degree (e.g. Masters, MBA, JD, MD) or 3 years of experience with a PhD in Computer Science or similar field in the financial services industry.
Hands-on experience in developing and supporting business applications for large corporations with experience in both batch and online systems
Experience in developing solutions using ETL tools like CloverDX, Talend, Ab Initio, Pentaho or other ETL Tool. Past project experience using CloverDX or Ab Initio preferred.
Experience working with Reporting tools like Jasper, MicroStrategy or Actuate. Past project experience using Jaspersoft or Actuate preferred.
Relational database and strong SQL development experience required; Experience with DB2 preferred.
Experience with Big data technologies and No-SQL database like Cassandra preferred.
Experience in shell scripting and strong knowledge of Perl or python scripting would be preferred
Development experience in a cross-platform, multi-tier environment and on ETL or Reporting production infrastructure.
Experience working on production issues as Level3/Level4 support in troubleshooting and provide a quick resolution.
Experience with scheduling tools like CA-ESP or Autosys desirable.
Basic knowledge of Java required.
Experience of using source code versioning system like SVN or GIT along with Continuous Integration and Deployment.
Strong communication skills with proven ability to present complex ideas and document in a clear and concise way.
Some basic mainframe knowledge is preferred.
Ability to develop code that follows established coding guidelines.
In-depth knowledge of the software development life cycle required.
Good knowledge on Dev, QA, production, processes and environments.
Good Knowledge of Software Configuration techniques and Code Promotion techniques

jobs_results.title: Fullstack Software Engineer
jobs_results.description:
Your job.

Live your passion for software development in exciting customer projects and be inspired by your colleagues’ enthusiasm. As a full-stack software engineer, you will cooperate with interdisciplinary teams in projects and experience how technology and team spirit unite to create innovative solutions. Your job will involve working closely with clients to develop, test, and ship software that meets their needs. You will efficiently and competently solve complex software challenges. Continuous further development and active knowledge exchange mean that you will be working with the latest methods and tools to stay up to date with the latest trends.

Our reputation is fundamental to our business, so our culture emphasizes quality, reliability and respect. We value learning new technologies and skills, thus, you will get a generous budget to attend conferences, participate in certified courses, and our annual technical camp is a lot of fun.

Your talent.
• You have a degree in... computer science or an equivalent related field (bachelor's/master's).
• You have proven expertise in the JavaScript ecosystem and used frameworks like ReactJS and Angular where you apply your in depth knowledge in JavaScript and/or TypeScript.
• You leverage your development workflow with tools like npm, webpack and Node.js.
• You have multiple years of experience with state-of-the-art web architectures and enjoy developing modern web applications.
• You value high quality code and you want to satisfy your thirst for knowledge of the latest technologies every day.
• You have professional experience in Java or the .NET stack for at least 3-4 years.
• You have a thorough knowledge of build and deployment of Full Stack applications, including practice with automated testing frameworks like Selenium, Jasmine or similar tools.
• You have professional experience working in an agile development environment. Ideally, you are a certified SCRUM developer or master.
• You have strong communication skills and like making decisions

Permanent Job

Job Description

Gamelogic started out with a small group of gaming enthusiasts and has since expanded into a full-fledged game development studio. As gaming enthusiasts, we are adamant about one thing: which is to have fun. We are experts in having a good time and we hope to offer fellow gamers a chance to unleash their inner child through our awesome games.

Our goal is to create innovative casual games that will penetrate the global market. Our team is made up of experienced game designers, programmers and artists and we are constantly looking to nurture the next generation of game developers.

When it comes to gaming for us at Gamelogic; the sky’s the limit.

------------------------

Title: Senior Game Programmer

Responsibilities:

· Brainstorming game concepts, design elements, and specifications with the game design team.

· Leading a team... of programmers and set work schedules and deadlines.

· Assist project leaders with statistical testing, and suggest new methods based on output.

· Selecting suitable game frameworks and translating concepts into clean and efficient code.

· Designing and testing gameplay features and prototypes.

· Generating game scripts and storyboards, as well as animating game characters and objects.

· Contributing to user interface development, as well as the integration of graphic design and audio features.

· Performing tests and implementing validation procedures.

· Documenting the full lifecycle of game development.

· Maintaining code, resolving issues, and performing bug fixes.

· Integrating the latest game industry trends into game designs.

· Working closely with a lead game developer to create task/project deliverables.

· Interface with Quality Assurance, Game Producers, Game Designers and Artists.

Requirements:

· Bachelor's degree in computer science, computer engineering, or similar.

· At least 5 years experience as a game programmer.

· Proficiency in Unity3D.

· Able to work in Windows, Linux and Mac environment.

· In-depth knowledge of full lifecycle game programming and related technologies.

· Highly proficient in programming languages, such as C++, C# and Java.

· Superb analytical and problem-solving skills.

· Excellent communication and collaboration abilities.

· Great organizational and time management skills.

· Able to troubleshoot and solve complex technical issues.

· Highly analytical with excellent written and verbal communication skills.

· Excellent time management skills with the ability to work under pressure to meet tight deadlines.

· Contribute to innovation in game design.

Bonus:

· Coursework or certification in game design and development preferred.
